{
  "text": "There are a number of other situations in which Littlewood-Richardson coefficients play a surprising role. These situations are thoroughly discussed in [CITATION_1] . We mention one of them here. Given a partition λ = (λ 1 , λ 2 , . . .) and a prime p, let G be a (finite) abelian p-group of type λ, i.e.,",
